==English==

===Etymology===
From the past participle of {{m|en|nim}}. The 'b' is a later addition to the spelling; it is not pronounced, and did not appear in the original word.

===Pronunciation===
* {{enPR|nŭm}}, {{IPA|/nʌm/|lang=en}}
* {{rhymes|ʌm|lang=en}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|er}}

# Without the power of sensation and motion or feeling; [[insensible]].
# Not able to react, [[surprised]], [[shocked]].
# Causing [[numbness]].
#* Shakespeare
#*: All thin and naked to the '''numb''' cold night.

